---
import DocPage from '../../../components/DocPage.astro'; import CodeBlock from '../../../components/CodeBlock.astro'; import Callout from '../../../components/Callout.astro';
const config = `{
  "mcpServers": {
    "gua": {
      "command": "bunx",
      "args": ["gui-mcp@latest", "mcp"],
      "env": {
        "GUA_BRIDGE_URL": "ws://127.0.0.1:8765",
        "GUA_ARTIFACT_DIR": ".gua"
      }
    }
  }
}`;
---
<DocPage eyebrow="TOOL / MCP SERVER" title="MCP Server" lead="gui-mcp is a thin stdio server that forwards an AI agent's tool calls to the WebSocket bridge running inside the game." description="Configure gui-mcp and operate a Gua game runtime." section="mcp">
  <h2>Start the game first</h2><div class="flow"><span>AI client</span><b>stdio →</b><span>gui-mcp</span><b>WebSocket →</b><span>Game bridge</span><b>→</b><span>Gua adapter</span></div><p>The MCP server does not own UI state. The Godot application must start a bridge listening at <code>ws://127.0.0.1:8765</code>.</p>
  <h2>Register it with an MCP client</h2><p>In a Bun environment, launch the published package with <code>bunx</code>. Adapt the following command and arguments to your client's configuration format.</p><CodeBlock title="Example MCP configuration" lang="json" code={config} /><Callout title="Connection and artifacts"><p>Set <code>GUA_BRIDGE_URL</code> for another port. Recordings, baselines, and visual artifacts default to <code>.gua</code>; change the root with <code>GUA_ARTIFACT_DIR</code>.</p></Callout>
  <h2>Inspect and operate semantic UI</h2><div class="grid-2"><div class="mini-card"><strong>get_ui_tree / wait_for_node</strong><p>Read the current tree and wait for node state changes.</p></div><div class="mini-card"><strong>click_node / focus_node</strong><p>Click or focus a Control by stable semantic ID.</p></div><div class="mini-card"><strong>set_value / set_checked / select</strong><p>Operate inputs, checkboxes, and selectable Controls semantically.</p></div><div class="mini-card"><strong>scroll / press_key</strong><p>Send scrolling or key input to a semantic target.</p></div><div class="mini-card"><strong>get_screenshot / get_logs</strong><p>Read the published PNG and runtime logs.</p></div><div class="mini-card"><strong>run_test</strong><p>Execute a small wait/click sequence.</p></div></div>
  <Callout kind="tip" title="Acceptance is not completion"><p>When the bridge returns a <code>requestId</code>, action tools wait for the correlated host completion event. Queue acceptance alone is not reported as success.</p></Callout>
  <h2>Recording and replay</h2><div class="grid-2"><div class="mini-card"><strong>start_recording / stop_recording</strong><p>Record semantic actions executed through MCP and return a schema v1 document.</p></div><div class="mini-card"><strong>save_recording / replay_recording</strong><p>Save under the artifact root and replay an inline, named, or most recent recording.</p></div></div><p>Sensitive <code>set_value</code> steps store only a <code>secretKey</code>. Replay resolves values from an in-memory <code>secrets</code> map. Coordinate fallback is rejected by default.</p>
  <h2>Visual comparison</h2><div class="grid-2"><div class="mini-card"><strong>compare_screenshot</strong><p>Compare the latest PNG against an explicitly named OS/renderer baseline. Baseline updates must be requested explicitly.</p></div><div class="mini-card"><strong>get_visual_artifacts</strong><p>Return paths for actual, expected, diff, and comparison manifest artifacts.</p></div></div>
  <h2>Prompting an agent</h2><CodeBlock title="Example prompt" lang="text" code={`Read the Gua UI tree and find the “Start Game” button.\nClick it by stable ID, then wait until “Loading...” is visible.\nIf the operation fails, inspect the logs and report both\nthe relevant UI tree state and the likely cause.`} />
  <Callout kind="warn" title="Do not ask for coordinate clicks"><p>Gua's value is semantic operation. Ask the agent to inspect <code>get_ui_tree</code> first, then act using ID, role, or text as evidence.</p></Callout>
</DocPage>
